rComments: Like all math profs at the uni, she's fine. Didn't really know how her mic worked cause it would get REALLY LOUD randomly and then really quiet the net second. Her notes are colour-coded and beautiful. She doesn't really explain things that well but I probably could've done better if I just bothered to do problems and go to her office hours.

Yea, calc two is rough. Wan yu was a good prof, didn't engage with students much but she got the job done. She's new to uottawa and is very compassionate towards her students, in terms of making extra time for office hours. The midterms were pretty light, but dont make the same mistake as I and judge the final by them. Hardest exam to date.

Honestly great prof! I second her ability to try her best to (successfully) convey the material and make it easier to grasp. She replies to emails very fast and is accessible outside of class. This year she had a rule of replacing your midterm marks with your final (given you do better of course). She always uploads her notes!
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: Un-stimulating during lectures but very detailed and makes understanding math much easier. She is accessible outside of class. Understanding and caring.

She is always active and enjoys her teaching, she will write lots of notes on the blackboard but later she will upload her beautiful notes. You do not have to go to her class just follow the notes, you can learn everything on it. Assignments are not very heavy you can do it with your friends in a group up to 4 members.
